ock","text":"in Rome.\r","standoffProperties":[{"id":"57bbb61f-77ee-4e2e-8a1b-3dbfc31e79ec","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":3,"end":6,"value":"501a8a32-2c8a-4934-9060-8c7e36339f0f","text":"Rom","metadata":{},"plugin":null,"isDeleted":false}],"blockProperties":[{"id":"645117ee-1016-403e-8663-312659f2ca92","type":"block/alignment","value":"right","metadata":{},"isDeleted":false}],"children":[],"metadata":{},"relation":{}},{"id":"953b3753-53ed-437d-804a-70fa3e3b9144","type":"standoff-editor-block","text":"\r","standoffProperties":[],"blockProperties":[],"children":[],"metadata":{},"relation":{}},{"id":"99d39cca-2911-4c33-84e3-9a4dcd1137c1","type":"standoff-editor-block","text":"Most Holy Father, — As intermediaries are very often the cause of serious misunderstandings I now ignore their assistance and write boldly to Your Holiness with reference to the tombs for San Lorenzo here. I have to say that I do not know which is preferable, the misfortune which turns to advantage, or the advantage which turns to misfortune. I am quite sure, witless and worthless though I am, that, if I had been allowed to go on as I began, all the marble for the said work would by now have been in Florence, blocked out in conformity with the requirements, and at a less cost than has already been incurred. It would have been a splendid work like the others I have finished.\r","standoffProperties":[{"id":"fd1c37a8-d6df-488c-a263-69f5d2669b75","type":"style/uppercase","start":0,"end":15,"value":"","text":"Most Holy Fathe","metadata":{},"plugin":null,"isDeleted":false},{"id":"56f77f05-e129-4214-a98b-60c67427b37d","type":"codex/meta-relation-reference","start":0,"end":15,"value":"a3a0420b-4702-457f-a7d5-b78153407c9c","text":"Most Holy Fathe","metadata":{},"plugin":null,"isDeleted":false},{"id":"38a27070-1383-4236-a08c-f949230bf5ec","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":5,"end":15,"value":"56a66a9e-ca50-45be-b8aa-aef2d47b5d96","text":"Holy Fathe","metadata":{},"plugin":null,"isDeleted":fal